## Plan Summary

**Bug:** Off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts`, line 7.

**Root Cause:** The loop condition `i < items.length - 1` stops one index short, so the last element is always skipped.

**Fix:** One-character change — remove the `- 1`:
```typescript
// Before (buggy)
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {

// After (fixed)
for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
```

**Impact:** 3 of 4 `processItems` tests currently fail. After the fix, all 6 tests should pass. The `sum` function is unaffected (it correctly uses `for...of`).

